Process Reengineering Agent (PRA)
Product Specification v1.1 (Complete)
1. Executive Summary

The Process Reengineering Agent (PRA) is a web-based AI tool designed for management consultants performing business process analysis and improvement work. It accepts multiple input types (interviews, process documents, process maps, strategy documents, event logs), creates a unified BPMN process model (current state and future state), and generates analysis, redesign recommendations, and client-ready deliverables for various levels of the business (i.e., Leadership, GMs, Management, Process Leads, COEs etc.,).

Deployment: Render (Web Services + PostgreSQL + Redis)
Target Users: Process consultants, business analysts, operations consultants

1.1 Primary Deliverables (Updated)

PRA must generate role-tailored deliverables as first-class outputs:

For GMs / Middle Management

Process Executive Overview Document

Process Context & Architecture Document

For Process Leads / COEs

Detailed BPMN Process Maps (L1–L6) — Current State + Future State

Activity Level Documentation

RACI Matrix

Controls & Risk Framework

Exception & Escalation Handling

Process Governance

Future State Improvement & Automation Opportunities Document (LEAN-based)

